<div id="pf4618" class="pf w51 h2f7" data-page-no="4618"><div class="pc pc4618 w51 h2f7"><div class="t m1160 xa9 h5 y2f46 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 4 July 20-26 </div><div class="t m303 x73 h10c y2c66 ff4 fs43 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MC2 52Ennufl </div><div class="t m1fa1 x27 h2d1 y2bb8 ff2 fs43 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">riEgin </div><div class="t m365 x40 h116 y2bb8 ff3 fs1b fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[LIS </div><div class="t m169e xd1 h5b y2bc3 ff4 fs23 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III </div><div class="t m1331 xc4 h5 y23a5 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;For I know that my Redeemer lives, </div><div class="t m2b1 xe h5 y2380 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and at last he will stand upon the </div><div class="t m833 x16 h5 y2351 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth; </div><div class="t m3a2 xc4 h5 yf14 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and after my skin has been thus </div><div class="t m5fd x16 h5 y207 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">destroyed, </div><div class="t ma38 x92 h5 y5cc ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then from my flesh I shall see </div><div class="t ma75 x16 h5 y484 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God, </div><div class="t m88c xc4 h5 y4be ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">whom I shall see on my side, </div><div class="t m713 x92 h5 y14a ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and my eyes shall behold, and not </div><div class="t m642 x16 h5 y557 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">another&quot; (Job 19:25-27, RSV). </div><div class="t m44f x0 h35 y5d0 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This lesson covers Job 12 through </div><div class="t m7af xd0 h35 y25f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20. It seems proper to skip lightly over </div><div class="t mb5b xd0 h35 y622 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these chapters, because so much that </div><div class="t m44e xd0 h35 yfdc ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is said by the three friends is repetition </div><div class="t m6cc xd0 h35 yb1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of what th6y have already said in the </div><div class="t m13c xd0 h35 ye1a ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">first dialogue. Someone has compared </div><div class="t m61a xd0 h35 yfc ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the speeches of Job&apos;s friends to a </div><div class="t m61e xd1 h35 y6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">series of wheels rotating on the same </div><div class="t m182 xd0 h35 y2a1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">axle. There is little progress, only </div><div class="t mdd4 xd0 h35 y1f7 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">restatement of the erroneous </div><div class="t m1842 xd1 h35 y8f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">traditions of their time. </div><div class="t mbd x0 h35 y5b6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s speeches are different. &quot;From </div><div class="t m112 xd1 h35 y34d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the depths of discouragement and </div><div class="t m234 xd1 h35 y87c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">despondency Job rose to the heights </div><div class="t me3 xd1 h35 y268 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of implicit trust in the mercy and the </div><div class="t ma23 xd1 h35 y107 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">saving power of </div><div class="t m8c x50 h35 y55d ff5 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God.&quot;—Prophets and </div><div class="t md06 xd0 h35 y38e ff5 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings, </div><div class="t m8fb x26 h35 y1a3 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 163. This spiritual progress </div><div class="t mb1a xd1 h35 y91b ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was slow and painful, but it can be </div><div class="t m845 xd1 h35 ye41 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">seen in the successive speeches of </div><div class="t ma43 xd1 h35 y421 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job. This lesson will pick up some of </div><div class="t m816 xd1 h35 y2057 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these evidences of dawn in the dark </div><div class="t me19 xd1 h35 y94e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">night of Job&apos;s sorrow. </div><div class="t m110a xb7 h35 y160 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It must be borne in mind that Job did </div><div class="t m993 xd1 h35 y251 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not have the slightest inkling of the </div><div class="t m9df xd4 h35 y99 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reasons for his suffering. He knew </div><div class="t mbbc xd4 h35 yc47 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nothing of the dialogue between the </div><div class="t ma80 xd4 h35 y220 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord and Satan. He did not know that </div><div class="t mb93 xd4 h35 y5dc ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he was a test case before the universe </div><div class="t ma08 xd4 h35 y36d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as to whether anyone really served </div><div class="t mbe2 xd4 h35 y1ab ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God out of pure loyalty and faith. </div><div class="t mb93 xb7 h35 y276 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It also must be remembered that Job </div><div class="t m3cf xd4 h35 y2cb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must not be judged on the basis of his  </div><div class="t mdfd x1f h35 y23a5 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">early discouragement or of his </div><div class="t m41f x1f h35 y238d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">repeated accusations against God. </div><div class="t m2e5 x1f h35 y1627 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Lord evaluated Job during those </div><div class="t m970 x1f h35 yf15 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trying months of anguish, not on the </div><div class="t m345 x1f h35 y207 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">basis of his questions and complaints, </div><div class="t m1317 x1f h35 y8ca ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but on the basis of what he would be </div><div class="t m5e6 x1f h35 y484 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">when he ultimately emerged from his </div><div class="t m1af x1f h35 y1c6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dark night. God sees His people, not </div><div class="t m79d x1f h35 y374 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as they are, but as they will be. He is </div><div class="t m825 x1f h35 y2b1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">like the parent who sees in the </div><div class="t m85b x1f h35 y7a8 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">immature child the eventual mature </div><div class="t m2b9 x1f h35 yd5 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">man or woman—only God&apos;s </div><div class="t m44d x1f h35 y2d9 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">foreknowledge is accurate and </div><div class="t m817 x1f h35 y260 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">complete. </div><div class="t m398 x1c h35 y244 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The </div><div class="t m7ca x78 h35 y243 ff5 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary </div><div class="t m82f x1f h35 y6e9 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">organizes the second dialogue, or </div><div class="t m662 x1f h35 y1d1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cycle, as follows (see vol. 3, p. 496): </div><div class="t m1fa4 x1c h35 yfc ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m9a7 xae h35 y494 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s first speech: he maintains </div><div class="t m2ab xae h35 y246 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his integrity, 12:1 to 14:22. </div><div class="t m7d6 x1c h35 y625 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m54e xae h35 y17a ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz&apos;s speech: he reproves </div><div class="t m20e xae h35 y337 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job for impiety, 15:1-35. </div><div class="t m210 x1c h35 yccb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m261 xae h35 ya6f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s second speech:, he accuses </div><div class="t m54b xae h35 y849 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his friends of being unmerciful, </div><div class="t ma3c xae h35 y34d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16:1 to 17:16. </div><div class="t ma7c x1c h35 yba ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m39a x86 h35 y5d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bildad&apos;s speech: he insists that </div><div class="t m247 x86 h35 y1a20 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">calamity overtakes the wicked, </div><div class="t m792 xae h35 y107 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18:1-21. </div><div class="t m854 x1c h35 y826 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m9a3 x86 h35 y37c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s third speech: he expresses </div><div class="t m195a x86 h35 y8e5 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his belief in the resurrection, </div><div class="t m792 xae h35 y134 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19:1-29. </div><div class="t m61e x5a h35 y234 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m708 xae h35 y234 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Zophar&apos;s speech: he describes </div><div class="t m9d9 x86 h35 y75e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the present and future </div><div class="t m8e1 x86 h35 y1396 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">punishment of the wicked, </div><div class="t m7b7 xae h35 y5d9 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20:1-29. </div><div class="t m9b4 x72 h5 ye07 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m23f x72 h5 y73 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t mb8b x6e h5 y72 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Sovereignty of God </div><div class="t m1126 xbc h5 y503 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 12:12-14, 17-21) </div><div class="t m558 x72 h5 y5dc ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m105c x6e h5 y443 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Problem of Death </div><div class="t mdf4 xbc h5 y5bc ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 14:10-13) </div><div class="t mb7 x72 h5 y491 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t ma0c x6e h5 y7c0 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Trust in Tradition </div><div class="t m5b1 xbc h5 y715 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 15:7-10) </div><div class="t m1ce x72 h5 y560 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t mdc9 x6e h5 y3c4 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Words Versus Warmth </div><div class="t mcfa xbc h5 y31 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:1-6) </div><div class="t m8a8 x72 h5 y880 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m43b xbc h5 y880 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An Intercessor </div><div class="t m220 xbc h5 y953 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:19; 19:25) </div><div class="t m2ef x72 h5 y35 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m772 xbc h5 y35 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Cry of Anguish </div><div class="t m42e xbc h5 ye1d ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 19:13-22) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
